Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2015 03:26:54 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Don't remove write right on generated file
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Without write right, non-clean build failed because the file
cannot be overwrite.

Signed-off-by: Aur√©lien Chabot <aurelien@chabot.fr>
---
 SConstruct | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/SConstruct b/SConstruct
index bf4e6b5..0e8470a 100644
--- a/SConstruct
+++ b/SConstruct
@@ -1264,7 +1264,6 @@ templated = [ x for x in templated if not x.startswith('debian/') ]

 for fn in templated:
     builder = env.Command(source=fn, target=fn[:-3], action=substituter)
-    env.AddPostAction(builder, 'chmod -w $TARGET')
     if fn.endswith(".py.in"):
         env.AddPostAction(builder, 'chmod +x $TARGET')

